84028,"Title":"A Saker and a Sea Gull","Artist":"Muhammad ibn Muhammad Shakir Ruzmah-'i Nathani; Zakariya ibn Muhammad Qazwini (ca. 1203-1283)","Date":"1121 AH/AD 1717 (Ottoman)","Medium":"ink and pigments on European laid paper","CreditLine":"Walters Art Museum, 1931, by bequest.","URL":"https://purl.thewalters.org/art/W.659.131A","ImageURL":"https://art.thewalters.org/images/raw/CPS_W.659.131a_Fp_DD.jpg"},{"ObjectID":31952,"Title":"Bouquet of Violets","Artist":"Léon Bonvin (French, 1834-1866)","Date":"1863","Medium":"watercolor with gum heightening, iron gall ink and pen, over graphite underdrawing on slightly textured, moderately thick, cream laid paper","CreditLine":"Walters Art Museum, 1931, by bequest.[1] In a diary entry Lucas records that Bonvin made 12 watercolors for William T. Walters in 1863. The commission was likely given on 12 February (see Randall, Diary of George A. Lucas, vol. 2, p. 150), on 14 October of the same year Lucas records \"Bonvin delivered the 12th flower for W's - paid him the remaining 100 fs making 300 fs for the 12\" (Randall, Diary of George A. Lucas, vol. 2, p. 163). This watercolor was likely hanging in Walters' Baltimore townhouse from 1885 (“The Walters Art Collection, Recent Additions – Barye, Millet, Bonnat – Bonvin’s Water Colors,” Baltimore Sun, 1 February 1886, p. 4.), described in R.B. Gruelle's catalogue of the gallery \"Notes Critical and Biographical\" (1895), p. 190.","URL":"https://purl.thewalters.org/art/37.1656","ImageURL":"https://art.thewalters.org/images/raw/PS4_37.1656_Fnt_DD_AT21_23645-tms.jpg"},{"ObjectID":35336,"Title":"Thistle in front of a Winter Landscape","Artist":"Léon Bonvin (French, 1834-1866)","Date":"1864","Medium":"watercolor with gum heightening, gouache, iron gall ink and pen, and graphite over graphite underdrawing on slightly textured, moderately thick, cream wove paper","CreditLine":"by bequest to Walters Art Museum, 1931,[1] In a diary entry for 13 February 1864 Lucas records \"Visit from Bonvin with 3 aquarelles, Salads, dessert & winter landscape\" (Randall, Diary of George A. Lucas, vol. 2, p. 172), given that there are no other watercolors of this subject from this date or before this date in Walters' collection, it is likely that this watercolor is the \"winter landscape\" Lucas descibes.","URL":"https://purl.thewalters.org/art/37.1519","ImageURL":"https://art.thewalters.org/images/raw/PS4_37.1519_Fnt_DD_AT21_23791 1-tms.jpg"},{"ObjectID":79140,"Title":"Tsuka with a Dragon","Artist":"Komori Harutoshi (Japanese, active ca. 1700)","Date":"ca. 1700 (early Edo)","Medium":"silver, gold, baleen","CreditLine":"Walters Art Museum, 1931, by bequest.","URL":"https://purl.thewalters.org/art/51.1154.3B","ImageURL":"https://art.thewalters.org/images/raw/PS3_51.1154.3b_Fnt_DD_JP09.jpg"},{"ObjectID":22176,"Title":"Initial U","Artist":"Peter Lombard; French","Date":"ca. 1180","Medium":"parchment with ink, paint and gold","CreditLine":"Walters Art Museum, 1985, by purchase.","URL":"https://purl.thewalters.org/art/W.809.3V","ImageURL":"https://art.thewalters.org/images/raw/PL7_W.809.3v_Fp_BW_T85.jpg"},{"ObjectID":36840,"Title":"Bes on Papyrus Column","Artist":"Egyptian","Date":"","Medium":"cast bronze","CreditLine":"Walters Art Museum, 1931, by bequest.","URL":"https://purl.thewalters.org/art/54.405","ImageURL":"https://art.thewalters.org/images/raw/ARG_54.405_Fnt_UK.jpg"},{"ObjectID":80456,"Title":"Leaf from Fieschi Psalter: Psalter Text","Artist":"Flemish","Date":"ca. 1275-1300","Medium":"ink and pigments on parchment","CreditLine":"by bequest to Walters Art Museum, 1931.","URL":"https://purl.thewalters.org/art/W.45.82R","ImageURL":"https://art.thewalters.org/images/raw/PS1_W.45.82R_Fnt_DD_T09.jpg"},{"ObjectID":14092,"Title":"Vase","Artist":"Chinese","Date":"late 17th century (Qing)","Medium":"porcelain with copper-red glaze","CreditLine":"by bequest to Walters Art Museum, 1931.","URL":"https://purl.thewalters.org/art/49.271","ImageURL":"https://art.thewalters.org